title: Critical Dell Data Lakehouse Flaw Allows Remote Attackers to Escalate Privileges

content.raw: Dell Technologies has disclosed a critical security vulnerability affecting its Data Lakehouse platform that could allow attackers with high-level privileges to escalate their access and compromise system integrity. The flaw, tracked as CVE-2025-46608, carries a maximum CVSS severity score of 9.1, indicating an exceptionally high risk to affected environments.
